{"TopicId":79717,"ForumId":46,"TopicTitle":"How to make Spoilers?","CreatedByName":"Hydrazine_Soup","CreatedById":91100,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-07-27T13:59:19Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Hydrazine_Soup","CreatedById":91100,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-07-27T13:59:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow can I make spoilers and place pics inside them?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 src=\u0022//s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/kerbal-forum-uploads/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-03-05T01:36:18Z\u0022 title=\u002203/05/2020 01:36  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 5, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Hydrazine_Soup\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lanrutcon","CreatedById":111982,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-07-27T15:28:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EPut the tag (spoiler=title) before and finish with (/spoiler).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENote:\u003C/strong\u003E Use [] instead of () and you can change the title of the spoiler.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExample:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode\u0022\u003E [spoiler=test123] hidden stuff [/spoiler] \u003C/pre\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003E hidden stuff \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003ETo add an image, the tag is (img), \u003Cstrong\u003Ejust like this:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENote:\u003C/strong\u003E must be a link to an image, aka direct link.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode\u0022\u003E [img=http://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/3477766576/f3115a4a3429aa502a0e7417567b8676.png] \u003C/pre\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/3477766576/f3115a4a3429aa502a0e7417567b8676.png\u0022 alt=\u0022f3115a4a3429aa502a0e7417567b8676.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIf you want an image in a spoiler, just put inside:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode\u0022\u003E [spoiler=Cool Image] [img=http://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/3477766576/f3115a4a3429aa502a0e7417567b8676.png] [/spoiler] \u003C/pre\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003E \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/3477766576/f3115a4a3429aa502a0e7417567b8676.png\u0022 alt=\u0022f3115a4a3429aa502a0e7417567b8676.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hydrazine_Soup","CreatedById":91100,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-07-27T16:31:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-03-05T01:36:02Z\u0022 title=\u002203/05/2020 01:36  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 5, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Hydrazine_Soup\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FreeThinker","CreatedById":117389,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-18T20:18:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EWhy isn\u0027t this included in the advanced editor mode. are there any other tags not found in the advanced editor mode?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"vexx32","CreatedById":12283,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-19T00:13:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/misc.php?do=bbcode\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EThere are a few.\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThey don\u0027t appear as buttons because adding additional buttons to the editor is significantly more difficult than just adding BBCode. If I recall correctly, it would require someone at Squad to FTP into the servers and upload thumbnails for use as the buttons. They are frequently too busy to do so, however.\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}